[32m+[m[32m## ADR-032 — Polyglot Binding Tiers (HTTP → UDS/RPC → FFI) (2026-07-04)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Status:** Accepted[m
[32m+[m[32m**Driver:** Continuation of `chore/l5-109-omniroute-fork-cleanup-2026-06-18` (L5-114)[m
[32m+[m[32m**Supersedes:** None (additive — extends ADR-031's "M4 evaluate in-process Go SDK vs sidecar" decision with a fleet-wide binding-tier policy)[m
[32m+[m[32m**MADR:** [`docs/adr/0032-polyglot-binding-tiers.md`](docs/adr/0032-polyglot-binding-tiers.md) (full MADR with per-edge binding map, benchmarks, and rollout)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Context[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mADR-031 fixed the **Tier-1 router** as `maximhq/bifrost` (Go, MIT, vendored at[m
[32m+[m[32m`vendor/bifrost/`) accessed over its **HTTP gateway** at[m
[32m+[m[32m`${BIFROST_BASE_URL}/v1/chat/completions`[m
[32m+[m[32m(`open-sse/executors/bifrost.ts:107-244`). The HTTP sidecar default is the[m
[32m+[m[32mright call for an **initial drop-in** because it preserves backwards[m
[32m+[m[32mcompatibility, isolates the Go process for kill-switch semantics[m
[32m+[m[32m(`open-sse/services/bifrostKillSwitch.ts:382-416`), and avoids requiring a[m
[32m+[m[32mNode ABI to talk to Go.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mBut the Phenotype fleet already has polyglot substrates that can be used[m
[32m+[m[32m**outside the Tier-1 router** to squeeze more out of the hot path:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Tokn** (`crates/tokn`, Rust, hexagonal routing — `pareto_router/ports/adapters`)[m
[32m+[m[32m  is converging into OmniRoute per `PLAN.md` § 5.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **phenotype-routing** (Rust, proposed rename of the ADR-001 "bifrost"[m
[32m+[m[32m  substrate per `docs/ROUTING-CONVERGENCE-STATUS.md:46`) is the canonical[m
[32m+[m[32m  Rust routing substrate.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **`dispatch-mcp`** (Go) is already a fleet-wide pattern.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **`pheno-go-ctxkit`** (Go, fleet-wide) is the canonical context/HTTP[m
[32m+[m[32m  substrate.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **`OmniRoute/crates/`** is the planned Rust entry-point per[m
[32m+[m[32m  `SPEC.md` § 13 / `PLAN.md` § 5.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe user directive (2026-07-04): **"consider polyglot with native ABI FFI or[m
[32m+[m[32msimilar direct bindings, or unix sockets/RPCs and others for hot modules/hot[m
[32m+[m[32mpaths and edges or other modules."**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThis ADR formalizes the **3-tier binding policy** that picks the cheapest[m
[32m+[m[32mbinding whose guarantees still match the workload.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Decision[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Three binding tiers, picked per-edge by a fixed decision rule:**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Tier | Mechanism | Overhead at p50 | Hot-path fit | Adoption |[m
[32m+[m[32m|---|---|---|---|---|[m
[32m+[m[32m| **T1 — HTTP sidecar** (default) | `fetch()` over TCP loopback (`BIFROST_BASE_URL`) | ~1-2 ms (loopback) | Tier-1 router, dashboards, ops endpoints | ✅ shipped (B1-B9, PR #95) |[m
[32m+[m[32m| **T2 — Unix-domain-socket (UDS) RPC** | JSON-RPC / Cap'n Proto / FlatBuffers over UDS, framed | ~50-200 µs (no kernel TCP) | High-RPS Tier-2 modules (compression, translator, semantic cache) | ☐ planned (Q3 2026, F1-F3) |[m
[32m+[m[32m| **T3 — Native ABI FFI** | `napi-rs` (Node↔Rust), `cgo` (Node↔Go), `pyo3` (Python↔Rust), `wasmtime` (any↔WASM) | ~1-10 µs (zero-copy) | Tight inner loops (SSE chunking, combo scoring, tokenization, regex prefilter) | ☐ planned (Q4 2026, F4-F6) |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Decision rule (per edge)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Is the call edge on the request hot path AND called > 100/sec/process?[m
[32m+[m[32m   - No  → T1 (HTTP sidecar). Default. Avoids FFI surface.[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Yes → continue.[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Does the edge need shared memory / zero-copy streaming?[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Yes → T3 (FFI). Hard constraint.[m
[32m+[m[32m   - No  → continue.[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Does the target language ecosystem provide a battle-tested RPC framework?[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Yes → T2 (UDS RPC). Default for cross-language RPC at high RPS.[m
[32m+[m[32m   - No  → T3 (FFI). Only if the workload also needs the perf.[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Mapping (per edge; 2026-07-04 baseline)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Edge | Language pair | Current | Recommended tier | Driver |[m
[32m+[m[32m|---|---|---|---|---|[m
[32m+[m[32m| Tier-1 router dispatch (Tier-2 → Tier-1) | TS ↔ Go | T1 (HTTP via `BifrostBackendExecutor.execute`) | **T1 (keep)** | Backwards-compat, kill-switch semantics, isolated Go process. |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Combo resolution (combo target list expansion) | TS (single process) | TS in-process | **T1 (keep)** | Pure-TS function; no cross-language call. |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Format translation (OpenAI↔Anthropic↔Gemini) | TS ↔ Rust | TS in-process (`open-sse/translator/`) | **T3 (FFI via `napi-rs`)** | Called every chat completion; pure-data transformation; hot path; minimal GC pressure. |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Prompt compression (lite / caveman / rtk) | TS (engine) | TS in-process (`open-sse/services/compression/`) | **T2 (UDS RPC) → T3 (FFI) when reaching 1k RPS** | Token-burn savings are real-time-budget-critical; pure-data I/O; well-framed. |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Semantic cache lookup | TS ↔ Rust | SQLite (`src/lib/db/reasoningCache.ts`) | **T3 (FFI → Rust tokenization + simhash)** | Vector math + regex prefilter is dominated by Rust perf. |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Signature cache lookup | TS in-process | SQLite | **T1 (keep)** | Already sub-ms; no perf gain. |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Rate limit / quota token-bucket (DEBT-001) | TS in-process | TS in-process (`open-sse/services/rateLimitManager.ts`) | **T3 (FFI → Rust `parking_lot`-based bucket)** | 1k+ RPS fairness-critical; lock-free bucket in Rust. |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Combo scorer (12-factor Auto-Combo) | TS in-process | TS in-process (`open-sse/services/autoCombo/scoring.ts`) | **T3 (FFI → Rust SIMD)** | Numerics-heavy; SIMD-accelerated scoring halves p99. |[m
[32m+[m[32m| SSE chunking (`open-sse/handlers/chatCore.ts:1042-1058`) | TS in-process | TS in-process `while(true)` loop | **T3 (FFI → Rust `futures::stream` or Go goroutine pool)** | Called per upstream byte; zero-copy wins compound. |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Webhook HMAC signing (`src/lib/webhookDispatcher.ts`) | TS in-process | TS in-process | **T1 (keep)** | Low RPS; correctness > perf. |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Reasoning replay (`open-sse/services/reasoningCache.ts`) | TS ↔ Rust | SQLite | **T3 (FFI → Rust `dashmap` + `bincode`)** | Memory-sharded hashmap + zero-copy serialize. |[m
[32m+[m[32m| A2A skill invocation (peer agent dispatch, ADR-004) | TS ↔ TS | HTTP (`POST /a2a`) | **T1 (keep)** | Cross-org RPC; already async-friendly. |[m
[32m+[m[32m| MCP server tool dispatch (Tier-2 → Tier-1 MCP client) | TS ↔ Go (Bifrost MCP client) | JSON-RPC over HTTP/SSE | **T2 (UDS RPC when co-located)** | Co-located deploys skip HTTP overhead. |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Provider model catalog (B4) | TS ↔ Go | HTTP `/v1/models` (cached in SQLite) | **T3 (FFI → Bifrost Go SDK)** | Already cached; refresh is cron-driven, not hot path. |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Pricing sync (`src/lib/pricingSync.ts`) | TS in-process | HTTP LiteLLM nightly cron | **T1 (keep)** | Cron, not hot path. |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Dashboard analytics rollups | TS ↔ SQLite | SQL via `better-sqlite3` | **T1 (keep)** | UI-bound, not perf-bound. |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Guardrail hot path (`src/lib/guardrails/`) | TS in-process | TS in-process | **T2 (UDS RPC → Rust `regex`/`aho-corasick`)** | PII-masker and prompt-injection are regex-heavy on every request. |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Why T2 (UDS RPC) over T3 (FFI) by default[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Process isolation** — UDS preserves the kill-switch semantics already[m
[32m+[m[32m  implemented in `open-sse/services/bifrostKillSwitch.ts`. A panicking Rust[m
[32m+[m[32m  or Go process via FFI takes down the whole Node process.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Ecosystem maturity** — Cap'n Proto, FlatBuffers, and `prost` (Protobuf)[m
[32m+[m[32m  all have stable Rust + Go + TS bindings and battle-tested framing.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **No ABI versioning burden** — FFI surfaces need `#[repr(C)]` discipline[m
[32m+[m[32m  + semver-pinned layouts; UDS RPC uses wire-format semver instead.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Cost-overhead fits hot path** — 50-200µs UDS loopback is an order of[m
[32m+[m[32m  magnitude under HTTP loopback (1-2ms) and within budget for non-[m
[32m+[m[32m  byte-by-byte workloads.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Why T3 (FFI) for the inner loops[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Zero-copy possible** — `napi-rs` `Buffer` is a direct view into the[m
[32m+[m[32m  Rust `Vec<u8>`; FlatBuffers over UDS still serializes per call.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Sub-10µs overhead** — required for byte-by-byte SSE chunking and SIMD[m
[32m+[m[32m  scoring where every microsecond compounds.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Lock-free primitives** — `parking_lot`, `dashmap`, `crossbeam` are[m
[32m+[m[32m  faster than anything achievable over IPC.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Rollout (F1-F6)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| ID | Item | Owner | Effort | Status |[m
[32m+[m[32m|---|---|---|---|---|[m
[32m+[m[32m| **F1** | Pick canonical UDS RPC framework (Cap'n Proto vs Protobuf vs FlatBuffers) | core | S | ☐ Q3 2026 |[m
[32m+[m[32m| **F2** | `crates/tokn` extraction + UDS RPC server (`open-sse/services/udsRpc.ts` client) | tokn | M | ☐ Q3 2026 |[m
[32m+[m[32m| **F3** | Migrate compression engine (lite/caveman/rtk) to UDS RPC | compression | M | ☐ Q3 2026 |[m
[32m+[m[32m| **F4** | `napi-rs` bindings for Rust SIMD combo scorer + regex prefilter | core + tokn | L | ☐ Q4 2026 |[m
[32m+[m[32m| **F5** | `napi-rs` bindings for Rust semantic cache + reasoning replay | core + tokn | L | ☐ Q4 2026 |[m
[32m+[m[32m| **F6** | `cgo` integration for in-process Bifrost Go SDK (Bifrost's v1.0 GA gate) | core | M | ☐ 2027 Q1 |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Consequences[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Positive:**[m
[32m+[m[32m- Per-edge cost discipline — T1 HTTP is no longer forced on edges where[m
[32m+[m[32m  T2/T3 dominates.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Phenotype-fleet convergence unblocked — `Tokn::tokenledger::routing` and[m
[32m+[m[32m  `crates/tokn` can land in OmniRoute without an HTTP detour.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Zero new ops surface — UDS RPC inherits the same process-isolation[m
[32m+[m[32m  guarantees as the HTTP sidecar.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Negative / Risks:**[m
[32m+[m[32m- **ABI versioning** — T3 FFI surfaces must be semver-pinned; ABI breaks[m
[32m+[m[32m  cause segfaults. Mitigated by `#[repr(C)]` + a `version()` symbol on[m
[32m+[m[32m  every FFI crate.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Process proliferation** — T2 UDS adds one process per language surface;[m
[32m+[m[32m  Mitigated by a single `omniroute-polyglot-host` supervisor process that[m
[32m+[m[32m  spawns N language servers on startup.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Build complexity** — `napi-rs` and `cgo` need Rust/Go toolchains on[m
[32m+[m[32m  the build host. Mitigated by the existing `Justfile` + per-platform[m
[32m+[m[32m  prebuilt artifacts (`dist/ffi/<triple>/`).[m
[32m+[m
