[32m+[m[32m### 2.5.4 v8.2 — Polyglot Binding Tiers (added 2026-07-04, ADR-032)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m> **Decision (ADR-032)**: extend ADR-031's HTTP sidecar default with a 3-tier[m
[32m+[m[32m> binding policy — T1 HTTP sidecar (default), T2 UDS RPC (high-RPS Tier-2),[m
[32m+[m[32m> T3 native ABI FFI (inner loops). Each call edge picks the cheapest binding[m
[32m+[m[32m> whose guarantees still match the workload. See[m
[32m+[m[32m> [`docs/adr/0032-polyglot-binding-tiers.md`](docs/adr/0032-polyglot-binding-tiers.md)[m
[32m+[m[32m> for the per-edge mapping and decision rule.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m#### 2.5.5 Why 3 tiers (and not FFI-everywhere or HTTP-everywhere)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Concern | T1 HTTP sidecar | T2 UDS RPC | T3 FFI |[m
[32m+[m[32m|---|---|---|---|[m
[32m+[m[32m| Process isolation | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ (same process) |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Zero-copy buffers | ❌ | ❌ (framed) | ✅ |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Build complexity | low | medium (`capnp`/`flatc`/`protoc`) | high (`napi-rs`/`cgo`/`pyo3`) |[m
[32m+[m[32m| ABI versioning burden | none | wire-format semver | `#[repr(C)]` discipline |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Overhead at p50 | ~1-2 ms | ~50-200 µs | ~1-10 µs |[m
[32m+[m
